By Robert Egbe Mothers of internet scammers in Lagos have formed an association, acting Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has revealed. Magu stated this at the commission’s Lagos Office at the ongoing EFCC stakeholders conference on crusade against cybercrime fraudsters. According to the anti-graft agency, the Lagos Office had made 300 cybercrime-related arrests since January and had secured 200 convictions. Details shortly…